OMG, this is so delicious. I served it instead of baked potatoes with a steak dinner. It was so good that I didn't want my steak. Definitely a recipe that you will want to make again and again.

Rating: 0
This is a four fork recipe! I have made it several times, and it is always consistently delicious. I did substitute non-fat Greek Yogurt for the cream, and that did not interfere with the flavor. When I make it for holidays, I add some chopped toasted pecans. I also use Gluten Free Flour and bread crumbs.

Rating: 4
Made this for supper tonight to accompany a pork roast. Absolutely outstanding recipe! Slight modifications made - didn't have half-and-half so used 1 2/3 cups 1% milk and the remainder whipping cream. By mistake I added 1/3 cup of grated parmigiano reggiano to the bread crumbs but no matter, it browned up nicely and the flavour of the cauliflower with the sauce was scrumptious! Husband loves cauliflower with cheese and this one was a hit! Will definitely make again!

